{"key":"processedPost-5106955","value":{"id":5106955,"first":5105619,"last":5107119,"when":1135613481,"utime":"12/26/05 06:11 PM","content":"You need to prevent moisture loss and allow for some CO2 buildup during colonization.  Rubbermaid bins work great, as do just about any container that will hold the straw.  I've had good luck filling up a small laundry basket with straw and spawn, then slipping it into a black plastic trash bag until full colonization, after which time it can be brought out and fruited either in an open room or small greenhouse.  <br />RR","title":"Re: Wrapping Straw"}}